verbose_text: Another photosynthetic leaf pigment, car, was also reduced by the negative effect of extreme pH, and compared to the control, a 30 and 16% reduction was observed in an acidic (pH 4.0 and pH 5.5, respectively) condition, while a 28% reduction in car content was found at in an alkaline (pH 8.5) condition (XREF_FIG d).
evidence: car, was also reduced by the negative effect of extreme pH
